Who are you,
and why are you at my desk?

12:05.300 --> 12:07.225
I'm Simon and Brittney's
sister, Tonya.

12:07.376 --> 12:09.469
Yup, there's a third twin.

12:09.621 --> 12:12.638
I'm kidding. I'm kidding.
I'm Tonya Lovewell.

12:12.791 --> 12:15.458
And I have got a bone
to pick with you.

12:15.551 --> 12:16.809
Let me guess,
you want more screen time

12:16.903 --> 12:18.144
for Simon and Brittney.

12:18.296 --> 12:19.812
You did them dirty
in that trailer.

12:19.965 --> 12:21.314
We all know that the twins

12:21.466 --> 12:23.224
are the most compelling cast
that you have.

12:23.243 --> 12:25.151
But let's look at this
in a different way.

12:25.303 --> 12:27.061
What can I do for you?

12:27.080 --> 12:29.063
Do you need more dance names
for your red carpet?

12:29.140 --> 12:30.081
No, no, I'm good.

12:30.233 --> 12:31.416
I'm gonna look through my DMs.

12:31.585 --> 12:32.992
I get you dance influencers,

12:33.144 --> 12:35.086
you point a camera
at my kids, deal?

12:35.313 --> 12:36.588
-No.
-(laughs)

12:36.739 --> 12:38.982
Please don't book anyone
or act like you represent

12:39.000 --> 12:40.925
the show in any way,
shape, or form.

12:41.152 --> 12:42.502
What is a show, Nick,

12:42.578 --> 12:44.504
except for transactions,
favors, and debts, am I right?

12:44.580 --> 12:45.746
I don't know
what you're saying.

12:45.840 --> 12:47.173
Well, get it done.

12:47.267 --> 12:48.916
-'Cause guess what.
-I'm not guessing.

12:48.935 --> 12:51.919
'Cause it's
the Lovewell love-way.

12:52.013 --> 12:54.497
Oh, ooh.
This is gonna be perfect.

12:54.516 --> 12:56.441
Hey, I'm just gonna park myself
right here.

12:56.592 --> 12:59.335
-That's where Brian sits.
-Not anymore.

12:59.354 --> 13:00.945
Okay.

13:01.097 --> 13:02.947
Hey. (sighs)

13:03.174 --> 13:04.265
NICK:
Millions will be watching.

13:04.509 --> 13:07.343
It's no big deal.
Try to act natural, all right?

13:07.362 --> 13:09.103
Zero pressure.
Let's do this, guys.

13:09.122 --> 13:10.196
WAYNE: So, Gabby,
you were given

13:10.290 --> 13:11.623
a second chance
to audition.

13:11.774 --> 13:13.182
-Was it worth it?
-Oh, I mean,

13:13.276 --> 13:15.034
It's been everything
I hoped for and more.

13:15.186 --> 13:16.944
I mean I won a car!
Oh, I'm so sorry.

13:16.963 --> 13:18.354
I'm not supposed say that,
am I?

13:18.373 --> 13:20.465
Gabby, take your energy
down 25%.

13:20.616 --> 13:23.376
How has being on the show
affected your life thus far?

13:23.528 --> 13:26.212
It's...different.

13:26.306 --> 13:28.139
That's all you've got to say?

13:28.308 --> 13:29.215
I mean--

13:29.367 --> 13:31.292
Please take your energy
up 50%.

13:31.311 --> 13:34.437
So who in the cast
surprises you?

13:36.299 --> 13:38.983
My sister Brittney
surprises me every day

13:39.210 --> 13:40.393
with her natural talent.

13:40.487 --> 13:43.880
My brother Simon
surprises me every day

13:43.898 --> 13:45.048
with his natural talent.

13:45.066 --> 13:47.900
-(slurping)
-Surprise, surprise.

13:47.994 --> 13:50.995
Have I felt overwhelmed
by<i> Swan Lake</i> choreo?

13:51.222 --> 13:52.405
-AJA: No way.
-Never.

13:52.499 --> 13:53.239
I can do it all.

13:53.482 --> 13:54.165
If anything,
I was underwhelmed.

13:54.334 --> 13:55.834
You were all underwhelmed

13:55.985 --> 13:58.744
by the timeless ballet classic
<i> Swan Lake?</i>

13:58.839 --> 13:59.912
-Yeah.
-Easy, actually.

14:00.065 --> 14:01.589
It's a little basic.

14:03.068 --> 14:04.175
Okay.

14:04.327 --> 14:07.403
(yelling) So the cast
is really great, super--

14:07.496 --> 14:09.681
Everybody,
please stop the work!

14:09.908 --> 14:12.241
Everybody just stop the work.

14:12.260 --> 14:13.500
Go ahead, please.

14:13.595 --> 14:16.429
MIKE: Yeah, it's just
a very positive environment.

14:16.581 --> 14:18.581
How will I juggle home life
and life on the show?

14:18.600 --> 14:20.674
Well, I...

14:20.694 --> 14:22.843
yeah, it's gonna be
damn difficult without--

14:22.863 --> 14:25.012
Don't tip the season,
Julia, please.

14:25.031 --> 14:26.364
It'll be fine.

14:26.533 --> 14:31.427
I am happily married and have
a super supportive husband.

14:31.446 --> 14:32.871
<i>The Big Leap</i> let me check
an important box

14:33.022 --> 14:34.038
on my bucket list,

14:34.190 --> 14:36.449
to dance again
after I was sick.

14:36.543 --> 14:39.210
It also let me say to others
in a similar situation

14:39.362 --> 14:41.270
that you're more
than a diagnosis.

14:41.289 --> 14:44.549
Finally, a coherent answer.

14:52.951 --> 14:54.017
JUSTIN: Hey.

14:55.286 --> 14:56.452
Hey.

14:56.545 --> 14:59.713
Should we talk
about what happened today?

14:59.882 --> 15:01.215
What happened today?

15:01.234 --> 15:03.142
(chuckles)
You're messing with me.

15:03.294 --> 15:05.219
What do you want, Justin?

15:05.238 --> 15:09.148
I'm talking about...our kiss.

15:09.300 --> 15:11.058
Yeah, that was just for fun.

15:11.077 --> 15:13.244
Haven't you ever
kissed somebody before

15:13.396 --> 15:14.895
just to see what it's like?

15:14.915 --> 15:18.324
<i> (dramatic music)</i>

15:18.476 --> 15:21.144
Well, actually, no.
Not exactly.

15:21.312 --> 15:22.403
You should.

15:22.422 --> 15:24.589
It's a great way
to test-drive the options.

15:26.167 --> 15:27.984
Okay, gotta go.

15:28.002 --> 15:31.679
<i> ♪ </i>

15:35.268 --> 15:36.583
JULIA: You were so amazing
during that Q&A.

15:36.678 --> 15:39.437
Seriously, the answers
that you gave, the stories,

15:39.588 --> 15:43.274
you were just--you were
articulate and persuasive,

15:43.501 --> 15:45.851
but--oh, my God.

15:45.946 --> 15:47.186
You know what?
I've changed my mind.

15:47.338 --> 15:49.096
Will you please talk
to my ungrateful daughter?

15:49.115 --> 15:50.673
Of course I'll talk
to your ungrateful daughter.

15:50.692 --> 15:52.008
-You will?
-Let's do it.

15:52.026 --> 15:53.009
All right, let's do it.

15:53.027 --> 15:54.452
There you go.

15:55.863 --> 15:57.104
Hi, Sophia.

15:57.123 --> 15:58.957
This is Paula, your mom's
friend from the show.

15:59.184 --> 16:00.959
I've heard so much about you.

16:01.186 --> 16:02.961
Listen, I can't wait
to meet you at the premiere,

16:03.112 --> 16:05.463
so I'm gonna send my driver
to pick up you and your sister,

16:05.614 --> 16:07.356
on the early side
so we have a lot of time

16:07.450 --> 16:09.450
on the red carpet
for videos with celebrities.

16:09.527 --> 16:12.470
And if you wanna make any stops
anywhere, just let him know.

16:12.621 --> 16:15.598
Fantastic.
See you soon.

16:16.459 --> 16:17.717
Oh, my gosh.

16:17.869 --> 16:21.204
Incentivize, flatter,
push an agenda: persuasion 101.

16:21.206 --> 16:22.814
It also helps
not to be her mother.

16:22.965 --> 16:23.982
Yeah, no kidding.

16:24.133 --> 16:25.632
That was amazing.
Thank you so much.

16:25.727 --> 16:27.151
(phone ringing)

16:27.303 --> 16:30.137
Oh, that's my doctor.
I gotta go.

16:30.156 --> 16:31.155
-Okay.
-Yeah.

16:31.307 --> 16:32.548
-Everything okay?
-Yeah, yeah.

16:32.641 --> 16:33.825
-I'll see you tomorrow.
-Okay, see you tomorrow.

16:33.976 --> 16:34.900
-Okay.
-Thanks.

16:34.995 --> 16:37.453
PAULA: Yeah. Hi.

16:42.002 --> 16:45.077
<i> (light music)</i>

16:45.230 --> 16:47.246
(Brittney sighs)

16:47.340 --> 16:51.083
So what was life like
on the boat?

16:51.236 --> 16:53.994
Was it isolating?
Did you make friends?

16:54.014 --> 16:55.847
Mom, maybe Brittney
doesn't wanna talk

16:56.074 --> 16:58.090
about that time in her life.

16:58.243 --> 17:00.409
-I wanna dance on a boat.
-Hey, dream big, baby.

17:00.503 --> 17:03.262
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
Wait, Gabby, what is that?

17:03.356 --> 17:06.098
Oh, that's me and my friends
in high school.

17:06.192 --> 17:08.526
We dressed up
as<i> High School Musical.</i>

17:13.366 --> 17:16.701
<i>♪ We're all</i>
<i>in this together ♪</i>

17:16.852 --> 17:22.540
<i> ♪ When we reach, we can fly,</i>
<i>know inside, we can make it ♪</i>

17:23.935 --> 17:26.452
<i> ALL:</i>
<i> ♪ Wildcats, sing along </i>

17:26.604 --> 17:29.547
<i> ♪ Yeah, you really got it</i>
<i> goin' on ♪</i>

17:29.774 --> 17:32.032
<i> ♪ Wildcats in the house </i>

17:32.052 --> 17:33.959
<i> ♪ Everybody say it now </i>

17:34.112 --> 17:36.612
<i> ♪ Wildcats everywhere </i>

17:36.705 --> 17:39.039
<i> ♪ Wave your hands</i>
<i> up in the air ♪</i>

17:39.133 --> 17:42.042
<i> ♪ That's the way we do it,</i>
<i> let's get to it ♪</i>

17:42.136 --> 17:43.561
<i> ♪ Time to show the world </i>

17:43.730 --> 17:45.063
-(laughter)
-GINA: Oh, my.

17:45.139 --> 17:47.623
What? I thought
you didn't watch movies.

17:47.716 --> 17:48.791
BRITTNEY: I don't,

17:48.884 --> 17:52.070
but my mom's boyfriend
at the time

17:52.297 --> 17:54.888
stalked Vanessa Hudgens,
and he made Simon and I

17:54.982 --> 17:56.966
watch it, like,
a million times.

17:57.059 --> 18:00.469
So he is in jail now.

18:00.563 --> 18:04.690
-I'm so sorry to hear that.
-That's awful.

18:04.842 --> 18:06.400
It's okay.

18:06.419 --> 18:09.328
That wasn't even
the worst guy she dated.

18:09.480 --> 18:12.148
Some of her exes
would steal money from us,

18:12.166 --> 18:15.334
or some would leave
without saying goodbye, so...

18:15.428 --> 18:18.912
My mom was not very good
at making decisions.

18:18.932 --> 18:21.157
We all try our best.

18:21.175 --> 18:22.825
-Have more pizza.
-BRITTNEY: Can't.

18:22.844 --> 18:26.162
My mom wants me in
a calorie deficit at all times.

18:26.180 --> 18:29.014
-Eat more pizza.
-(laughs)

18:29.167 --> 18:32.168
Eat more pizza.

18:32.186 --> 18:33.185
Yeah,
she doesn't have to know.

18:33.279 --> 18:35.688
Hey, your secret's safe
with us.

18:35.840 --> 18:39.342
<i> (soft music)</i>

18:39.360 --> 18:41.636
-JOEL: To the premiere!
-To the premiere!

18:41.638 --> 18:42.745
Aah!

18:44.515 --> 18:47.125
Another round, please.
Thank you.

18:47.352 --> 18:49.276
Take it easy.
You don't wanna be hungover.

18:49.295 --> 18:51.036
-We are celebrating.
-Yeah.

18:51.131 --> 18:53.689
Tomorrow the world
gets to meet Mike Devries,

18:53.824 --> 18:57.543
the guy who joined a dance show
to win his wife back.

18:57.695 --> 18:58.952
Didn't work.

18:58.972 --> 19:00.363
Okay, well, all right.
We get it.

19:00.381 --> 19:02.122
And here's the must-see TV.

19:02.142 --> 19:04.124
Ole Mike falls
for another woman on the show,

19:04.218 --> 19:06.811
happens to be the evil
corporate overlord

19:06.962 --> 19:08.521
who fired him.

19:09.965 --> 19:12.391
-You hit me!
-You're being a giant baby.

19:12.543 --> 19:15.227
Where in<i> Daring Greatly</i>
does it say to hit people?

19:15.396 --> 19:17.321
Brené Brown
would've slapped you too.

19:17.473 --> 19:19.657
I don't know how much longer
I can sit here

19:19.808 --> 19:20.883
and watch you like this.

19:20.902 --> 19:22.994
You gotta move on.

19:23.145 --> 19:24.387
The rest of the world has.

19:24.405 --> 19:25.997
What's that supposed to mean?

19:26.224 --> 19:27.556
Paige is pregnant.

19:27.650 --> 19:30.168
Marie ran into her at Kmart.

19:30.319 --> 19:33.896
Pregnant?
With Patrick?

19:33.989 --> 19:36.081
-That was quick.
-Who cares?

19:36.234 --> 19:38.843
You realize how hard it is
to find happiness

19:39.070 --> 19:41.179
and somebody
who cares about you?

19:41.330 --> 19:43.997
Paula made you happy.

19:44.017 --> 19:46.333
Paula cared about you.

19:46.352 --> 19:49.503
So what?
She was doing her job.

19:49.522 --> 19:53.416
Now, you can be an angry
old man nursing grudges,

19:53.434 --> 19:57.344
or you could be a happy guy
in love with a beautiful woman.

19:57.363 --> 19:59.939
Oh, it's a difficult decision.

20:00.033 --> 20:01.440
Which one should I choose?

20:01.592 --> 20:04.017
Life is happening.

20:04.037 --> 20:06.495
Go embrace it, jackass.

20:09.709 --> 20:11.116
What are you drawing?

20:11.211 --> 20:13.252
It's for you,
but I'm not done yet.

20:14.288 --> 20:16.714
Are you gonna come
to the premiere?

20:16.941 --> 20:18.107
It's past my bedtime.

20:18.200 --> 20:20.384
You have a bedtime?
That's lame.

20:20.536 --> 20:22.595
Okay, check it out.

20:24.966 --> 20:26.724
Like it?
Yeah?

20:26.951 --> 20:28.392
You got any more
of these around here?

20:28.619 --> 20:31.479
There's more
coloring books there.

20:32.732 --> 20:37.142
<i> ♪ </i>

20:37.237 --> 20:39.462
GABBY: So I have
vanilla and strawberry.

20:39.555 --> 20:41.906
-Can I please have vanilla?
-Yup.

20:42.057 --> 20:44.800
<i> ♪ </i>

20:44.893 --> 20:45.993
Brittney?

20:48.397 --> 20:51.991
You know what?
I cannot do lactose.

20:52.085 --> 20:54.827
And I just remembered
that I have a thing.

20:54.996 --> 20:56.662
Thank you for dinner.

20:56.814 --> 20:57.904
Okay.

20:57.999 --> 21:00.925
<i> ♪ </i>

21:01.152 --> 21:02.927
She ate so much cheese.

21:03.078 --> 21:05.488
She's in for a long,
violent night.

21:05.506 --> 21:07.431
JESSICA: The live truck
just entered Pennsylvania.

21:07.583 --> 21:10.250
It should be here
afternoon to night-ish.

21:10.270 --> 21:11.844
Mm-hmm, so an hour
before we go live.

21:11.996 --> 21:13.512
Are you trying to kill me?

21:13.664 --> 21:16.089
It just do--
no, don't--do not tell me.

21:16.109 --> 21:18.667
-JLo dropped out.
-No, no!

21:18.686 --> 21:20.945
-No, I'm not hearing that, no.
-I just need to know--

21:21.096 --> 21:22.655
NICK: No.

21:29.196 --> 21:31.104
-JLo dropped out?
-NICK: Mm.

21:31.124 --> 21:32.181
You know, Wayne and I
have danced in front

21:32.199 --> 21:33.182
of thousands of people
every night

21:33.275 --> 21:34.533
for most of our lives.

21:34.627 --> 21:37.186
I'm sure we can read some
questions off a teleprompter,

21:37.279 --> 21:39.112
and I can pretend
to be warm and charming.

21:39.132 --> 21:40.189
A live show needs
something extra.

21:40.191 --> 21:41.299
It needs a different energy.

21:41.450 --> 21:43.301
It needs another voice, okay?

21:43.528 --> 21:44.802
You've produced
live television before.

21:44.953 --> 21:46.362
Why are you so on edge?

21:46.380 --> 21:48.697
I'm never gonna live down
<i> Atlantis,</i> all right?

21:48.716 --> 21:50.533
Pretty soon, I'm gonna be doing
a dumb dating show

21:50.701 --> 21:52.125
or a show with animals

21:52.219 --> 21:53.293
or a dumb dating show
with animals.

21:53.462 --> 21:55.146
And I'm gonna die alone
in my car,

21:55.297 --> 21:58.131
and no one's gonna clap for me
during the in m--

21:58.151 --> 22:00.876
the dead people part
of the Emmys.

22:00.895 --> 22:03.045
That's not
what this is about.

22:03.214 --> 22:04.396
If I don't pull this off,

22:04.549 --> 22:06.640
I don't know
if I'm gonna work again.

22:06.734 --> 22:08.233
My daughter already
thinks I'm a clown.

22:08.328 --> 22:10.161
I can't be
an unemployed clown.

22:10.312 --> 22:11.662
She won't have
any respect for me.

22:11.889 --> 22:14.314
<i> ♪ </i>

22:14.334 --> 22:16.167
You know, when I feel
the way you're feeling,

22:16.318 --> 22:18.985
there's a little mantra
that I like to say

22:19.005 --> 22:21.154
just to help
pull myself out of it.

22:21.174 --> 22:22.340
Oh, yeah?
What is it?

22:22.491 --> 22:24.083
Get up,
you stupid little bitch!

22:24.159 --> 22:25.509
You'll do whatever's asked
of you, and you do not get

22:25.661 --> 22:28.420
any food or water
until the job is done.

22:28.514 --> 22:30.089
-God, what is wrong with you?
-MONICA: What's wrong with you?

22:30.241 --> 22:31.849
Get up.
Figure it out.

22:32.000 --> 22:33.425
You have a live TV show
to produce.

22:33.594 --> 22:35.353
See you tomorrow morning.

22:35.580 --> 22:38.672
<i> (lively percussive music)</i>

22:38.766 --> 22:40.691
<i> ♪ </i>

22:40.843 --> 22:42.485
(exhales heavily)

22:43.588 --> 22:44.511
Get up,
you stupid little bitch.

22:44.530 --> 22:46.012
You'll do whatever's
asked of you,

22:46.107 --> 22:48.607
and you won't get any food
or water until the job is done.

22:48.684 --> 22:51.660
(breathes deeply)

22:52.855 --> 22:59.418
<i> ♪ </i>

23:02.790 --> 23:05.774
Six sugars, not five,
not seven, six.

23:05.793 --> 23:07.033
Okay, yes.

23:07.111 --> 23:08.219
-And, Alan?
-Yes?

23:08.370 --> 23:10.513
-I'll know.
-Okay.

23:11.782 --> 23:12.973
BRITTNEY: Mommy.

23:14.727 --> 23:16.060
You were right.

23:16.211 --> 23:18.729
Reggie didn't wanna focus
on football.

23:18.881 --> 23:20.380
It was Gabby.

23:20.474 --> 23:22.883
<i> (somber music)</i>

23:22.977 --> 23:25.794
(sighs)
Come here.

23:25.888 --> 23:27.905
<i> ♪ </i>

23:28.074 --> 23:30.466
All we've got is family.

23:30.484 --> 23:32.284
<i> ♪ </i>

23:32.394 --> 23:34.136
Last week when we visited
Gabby's high school,

23:34.155 --> 23:35.246
I heard something.

23:35.397 --> 23:38.374
<i> ♪ </i>

23:42.255 --> 23:43.979
-Excuse--what is this?
-Who are these people?

23:43.998 --> 23:47.073
Happy premiere day, huh?

23:47.093 --> 23:48.484
-Oh, God.
-You didn't sleep.

23:48.577 --> 23:49.910
Sleep?
What do I look like to you?

23:49.929 --> 23:51.762
A basic cable
or streaming service producer?

23:51.914 --> 23:53.322
I have a broadcast

23:53.340 --> 23:54.432
reality show to produce--
I mean, look.

23:54.583 --> 23:57.101
-It's a big truck.
-It's a live truck.

23:57.328 --> 23:58.827
This baby is state of the art,

23:58.846 --> 24:00.996
ready to broadcast to
an audience all across America.

24:01.089 --> 24:02.422
It was in New York
ten hours ago.

24:02.442 --> 24:03.682
I had to finagle
police escorts

24:03.834 --> 24:06.001
across most of Pennsylvania
and parts of Ohio.

24:06.170 --> 24:07.260
And how does one do that?

24:07.354 --> 24:08.446
Well, let's just say
you two will be

24:08.597 --> 24:10.172
appearing at a lot
of state fairs this summer.

24:10.191 --> 24:11.615
Come on, follow me.

24:12.510 --> 24:13.859
So your script should be
flying in any second now.

24:14.028 --> 24:15.344
Dante, script!

24:15.362 --> 24:17.029
So I timed out
the video packages

24:17.123 --> 24:18.197
and the Q&A segment myself.

24:18.291 --> 24:19.290
-DANTE: Script.
-Thank you. Here you go.

24:19.517 --> 24:22.017
Alan and I emulated
the rhythm and cadence

24:22.110 --> 24:23.294
of both of your voices--
show 'em, Alan.

24:23.445 --> 24:24.536
(with English accent)
I'm stunningly beautiful,

24:24.630 --> 24:25.963
but for some reason,
I'm angry all the time.

24:26.114 --> 24:27.465
Yeah, and then I timed it

24:27.616 --> 24:28.966
with the stopwatch
hanging around my neck.

24:29.117 --> 24:30.025
Do you guys see my stopwatch?

24:30.118 --> 24:31.376
Anyway, once the cast arrives,

24:31.529 --> 24:34.379
we'll get 'em prepped,
hair, makeup, wardrobe,

24:34.532 --> 24:37.049
yada, yada, yada,
you know, red carpet ready.

24:37.201 --> 24:39.368
Hey, speaking of red carpet,
what do you got?

24:39.461 --> 24:41.512
-ALLY: Confirmed guest list.
-NICK: That's what I wanted.

24:41.588 --> 24:43.388
WAYNE: Nick, how much coffee
have you had?

24:43.483 --> 24:44.482
All of it.
I had all the coffee.

24:44.709 --> 24:46.650
Plus Alan and I had
some of his Adderall.

24:46.877 --> 24:48.210
Hell yeah, we did, whoo!

24:48.303 --> 24:50.136
Oh, by the way,
meet our guest host.

24:50.231 --> 24:51.822
-Reggie's the guest host?
-NICK: Yeah.

24:51.991 --> 24:53.048
Sometimes thinking
outside the box

24:53.141 --> 24:54.992
means you gotta look
inside the box.

24:55.219 --> 24:56.385
Oh, my God, Alan,
write that down.

24:56.403 --> 24:57.995
-It's so good.
-So good.

24:58.146 --> 24:59.388
-ALAN: Oh, my God.
-Yeah, yeah, yeah.

24:59.481 --> 25:00.831
-Where do you want me, Nick?
-Just on that mark.

25:00.983 --> 25:02.166
Thank you, Reggie.

25:02.243 --> 25:03.167
Reggie, are you sure
you can do this?

25:03.318 --> 25:04.985
What, ask questions on TV?

25:05.004 --> 25:06.152
Yeah, I'm pretty sure
I got this.

25:06.247 --> 25:08.247
He's gonna kill it.

25:08.399 --> 25:10.299
(all gasp)

25:11.660 --> 25:14.261
ALAN (echoing):
Nick, stay away from the light.

25:16.999 --> 25:19.241
There he is.
There's my guy.

25:19.334 --> 25:20.333
We thought we lost you.

25:20.427 --> 25:21.835
Zach, I didn't know
you were coming.

25:21.854 --> 25:23.503
Of course.

25:23.523 --> 25:24.522
Had to make sure everything
goes off without a hitch.

25:24.673 --> 25:26.172
We're off to a bumpy start.

25:26.267 --> 25:27.358
Okay.
Alan, what are you doing?

25:27.509 --> 25:29.268
I was a lifeguard
at Raging Waters.

25:29.362 --> 25:31.177
I'm trying to see
if you have a concussion.

25:31.197 --> 25:32.345
Follow my finger.

25:32.365 --> 25:34.273
Oh, your hand smells.
Get away from me.

25:34.349 --> 25:35.682
-(Nick groans)
-Is he gonna be right?

25:35.776 --> 25:37.426
I think he needs to go
to the hospital.

25:37.519 --> 25:40.204
Absolutely,
he needs to go to the hospital.

25:40.431 --> 25:42.355
Health is wealth.
We can't get another Nick.

25:42.375 --> 25:44.375
But we also can't get
another premiere.

25:44.602 --> 25:46.210
So let's not burden
the hospital with that.

25:46.361 --> 25:47.878
-Sounds fine. Looks fine.
-Okay.

25:48.030 --> 25:48.862
-ZACH: He's fine.
-NICK: I'm good.

25:48.956 --> 25:50.047
Look at that, see?

25:50.198 --> 25:51.715
-You're helping him stand.
-Not very much.

25:51.942 --> 25:52.883
He's clearly concussed.

25:53.035 --> 25:54.385
Were you a lifeguard
at Raging Waters?

25:54.612 --> 25:56.053
Okay guys, guys,
I'm not going to the hospital.

25:56.204 --> 25:57.446
I have a show to produce.

25:57.464 --> 25:58.556
Alan, out of the way.
I'm going to the truck.

25:58.632 --> 26:00.540
Okay, just don't look
at any screens.

26:00.560 --> 26:02.726
Alan, that's my whole job,
looking at screens.

26:04.897 --> 26:05.896
I'm okay.

26:06.048 --> 26:08.624
Just a change right here.

26:08.717 --> 26:10.067
Just wanna be aware of that.
You see that change?

26:10.294 --> 26:11.602
Make sure you've got that.

26:11.754 --> 26:14.980
If you have any questions,
you can reach out to me.

26:15.074 --> 26:16.907
Excuse me one sec.

26:17.059 --> 26:17.908
What are you up to?

26:18.018 --> 26:19.243
Have you talked
to your sister?

26:19.394 --> 26:21.153
She was distraught all night
over that football player.

26:21.247 --> 26:22.471
Yeah, I'm sure
she'll be just fine.

26:22.564 --> 26:25.140
-What are you up to?
-I don't like your tone.

26:25.142 --> 26:26.642
But if you must know,
I have a deal with Nick.

26:26.660 --> 26:29.995
-Nick made a deal with you?
-Yes, he loves me.

26:30.089 --> 26:31.088
Brittney didn't have
any questions in the Q&A.

26:31.315 --> 26:35.667
Now she has one,
if that's okay with you.

26:35.744 --> 26:39.154
Just please, please,
don't do anything crazy, okay?

26:39.323 --> 26:41.557
This is really
important to us.

26:42.993 --> 26:46.228
Come here, hey.

26:47.498 --> 26:50.441
You know that I want
the best for you, right?

26:53.112 --> 26:56.096
I know you're upset
over Justin,

26:56.115 --> 26:57.781
but I'm just looking out
for you and Brittney

26:57.933 --> 27:02.361
because I love you more
than anything in the world.

27:02.513 --> 27:05.939
And we have
to stick together, right?

27:06.033 --> 27:08.851
-Right.
-Come here.

27:08.869 --> 27:10.628
You're my baby boy.

27:10.779 --> 27:12.379
I love you, Mommy.

27:14.467 --> 27:15.874
Gabby, we needed you
in hair and makeup,

27:15.968 --> 27:16.950
like, 30 minutes ago.

27:17.044 --> 27:18.118
Sorry.
Have you seen Brittney?

27:18.137 --> 27:19.285
No, why?
Do you need something?

27:19.380 --> 27:20.787
Yeah.
Could you give her this?

27:20.806 --> 27:22.047
It's a little gift
for the premiere.

27:22.199 --> 27:23.031
-Yeah.
-Thank you, okay, okay.

27:23.125 --> 27:24.383
We're over here?

27:24.477 --> 27:26.810
All right, pretty people
arriving and smiling.

27:26.962 --> 27:28.228
Ow.

27:29.556 --> 27:32.040
What--why are you doing that?
Can you stop that?

27:32.134 --> 27:33.150
You said you have
a show to produce.

27:33.301 --> 27:35.377
-Well, I do, but--
-I'm saving your life.

27:35.396 --> 27:37.655
-Oh, okay.
-(both laugh)

27:37.806 --> 27:39.548
ZACH:
Who's ready to shoot this?

27:39.717 --> 27:42.308
When I say<i> Big,</i> you say<i> Leap.</i>
<i> Big--</i>

27:42.328 --> 27:43.385
-Ugh, I'm leaving.
-ALL:<i> Leap.</i>

27:43.404 --> 27:44.736
I'll see you
on the other side.

27:44.889 --> 27:49.208
If he falls asleep and dies,
the blood's on your hands.

27:51.504 --> 27:53.486
-Amazing red carpet so far.
-Yeah.

27:53.506 --> 27:56.340
Reggie as host?
Inspired choice.

27:56.567 --> 27:57.490
Thank you.

27:57.584 --> 28:00.344
All we got to do now,
make it good.

28:00.495 --> 28:03.255
<i> SINGER: ♪ Ain't no mountain</i>
<i> high, no valley low ♪</i>

28:03.407 --> 28:06.425
<i> ♪ No river wide enough, baby </i>

28:06.501 --> 28:08.093
<i> ♪ If you need me, call me </i>

28:08.245 --> 28:12.414
<i> ♪ No matter where you are,</i>
<i> no matter how far ♪</i>

28:12.433 --> 28:16.084
<i> ♪ Just call my name,</i>
<i> I'll be there in a hurry ♪</i>

28:16.178 --> 28:18.344
<i> ♪ You don't have to worry </i>

28:18.364 --> 28:21.181
<i> ♪ Ain't no mountain</i>
<i> high enough ♪</i>

28:21.200 --> 28:22.441
<i> ♪ Ain't no valley low </i>

28:22.593 --> 28:24.943
30 seconds to air.
Host last looks.

28:25.095 --> 28:28.188
<i> SINGER: ♪ Ain't no river</i>
<i> wide enough ♪</i>

28:28.207 --> 28:29.522
What prevents us, people?

28:29.542 --> 28:31.600
It's a live show,
and it's not time yet.

28:31.693 --> 28:33.118
Kidding.
Keep loose out there, guys.

28:33.270 --> 28:35.028
We only got one shot at this.
Everybody have a good show.

28:35.122 --> 28:36.772
Nick, Nick!
I don't have my glasses.

28:36.790 --> 28:39.365
Wardrobe doesn't have them.
I don't know where they are.

28:39.385 --> 28:41.109
<i> NICK: All right, well,</i>
<i> can you read without 'em?</i>

28:41.128 --> 28:43.170
I can't even see my hands
in front of my face.

28:43.280 --> 28:44.446
Okay, 20 seconds to air.

28:44.539 --> 28:47.725
Okay, we need high energy
from the audience!

28:47.952 --> 28:50.227
(cheers and applause)

28:50.454 --> 28:51.895
<i> NICK: Alan, I need you to go</i>
<i> to Wayne's room,</i>

28:52.047 --> 28:53.305
<i> find his glasses,</i>
<i> and fly 'em back</i>

28:53.457 --> 28:56.049
<i> in the next 15 seconds,</i>
<i> or the show is ruined.</i>

28:56.068 --> 29:01.387
<i> SINGER: ♪ Baby, my love is</i>
<i> alive way down in my heart ♪</i>

29:01.407 --> 29:03.407
-I don't see 'em!
<i> -NICK: Did you check his desk?</i>

29:03.634 --> 29:05.817
<i> SINGER: ♪ And if you need</i>
<i> a helping hand ♪</i>

29:05.970 --> 29:08.804
<i> ♪ I'll be there on the double</i>
<i> just as fast as I can ♪</i>

29:08.822 --> 29:10.080
Ooh, God.

29:10.307 --> 29:12.249
Move it, Alice!
Sorry, Alice!

29:13.310 --> 29:14.752
<i> -NICK: Get 'em in there.</i>
-Move!

29:14.903 --> 29:16.979
<i> SINGER:</i>
<i> ♪ Ain't no valley low </i>

29:16.997 --> 29:19.481
<i> ♪ Ain't no river wide enough </i>

29:19.574 --> 29:22.408
<i> ♪ To keep me from getting</i>
<i> to you ♪</i>

29:22.428 --> 29:26.430
JESSICA:
In five, four, three, two.

29:26.581 --> 29:29.415
America, we are
live from Detroit.

29:29.435 --> 29:31.101
<i> MONICA: Good evening.</i>
<i> I'm Monica Sullivan.</i>

29:31.253 --> 29:32.661
<i> WAYNE:</i>
<i> And I'm Wayne Fontaine.</i>

29:32.754 --> 29:35.773
BOTH: Welcome
to<i> The Big Leap After Show.</i>

29:36.000 --> 29:38.650
(cheers and applause)

29:42.615 --> 29:44.356
<i> JESSICA: All right, everyone.</i>
<i> I've got Reggie on his mark.</i>

29:44.508 --> 29:46.950
All right, everybody
stand by for Q&A.

29:47.102 --> 29:50.287
And three, two.

29:50.514 --> 29:51.955
Welcome back!

29:52.182 --> 29:54.274
During the premiere,
you all watched

29:54.293 --> 29:56.201
as we selected
the Big Leap Dance Company.

29:56.370 --> 30:00.022
Monica, is it time
to talk to the cast?

30:00.040 --> 30:02.207
Oh, it's time.
I'm ready.

30:02.301 --> 30:05.027
But first, we have
a very special guest.

30:05.045 --> 30:06.545
You know him
from his nine seasons

30:06.697 --> 30:07.954
as a tight end
for the Detroit Lions.

30:07.973 --> 30:10.974
But at our dance studio,
we simply know him as Reggie.

30:11.201 --> 30:13.844
Ladies and gentlemen,
Reggie Sadler.

30:13.979 --> 30:16.313
Let's go, Detroit!
Come on, baby!

30:16.464 --> 30:19.207
How we doing, fellas?
You all right?

30:19.226 --> 30:20.967
That's right.
I'm here for y'all, baby!

30:20.986 --> 30:23.821
Oh, oh!
Hit 'em with the...

30:23.972 --> 30:25.063
I see you, boy.

30:25.215 --> 30:27.049
What up, family?
Y'all good?

30:27.067 --> 30:28.641
<i> -All right.</i>
-See that?

30:28.661 --> 30:30.385
You cannot teach that.
It gives me chills.

30:30.554 --> 30:31.903
REGGIE: I think
what impressed me the most

30:31.997 --> 30:33.479
was the talent
in this cast.

30:33.499 --> 30:35.833
I mean, I can barely even begin
to describe the dancing.

30:35.984 --> 30:37.225
You know what?

30:37.319 --> 30:39.169
I think maybe we should
just take a look, huh?

30:39.321 --> 30:40.820
You heard him.
Let's take a look.

30:40.840 --> 30:43.990
<i> (upbeat music playing)</i>

30:44.084 --> 30:45.901
Brittney, Brittney,
Brittney, hi.

30:45.994 --> 30:47.252
I got you a present.

30:47.346 --> 30:49.162
It's no big deal,
but Jessica has it.

30:49.256 --> 30:50.922
-Great, thanks.
-GABBY: Okay.

30:51.091 --> 30:52.240
Oh, I hope
the pizza last night

30:52.334 --> 30:55.835
didn't make you
too gassy or bloated.

30:56.004 --> 30:59.039
(cheers and applause)

30:59.766 --> 31:02.675
Well, Simon, you're one
of our ballroom dancers.

31:02.695 --> 31:06.922
Is there anyone in the cast
who surprised you?

31:07.015 --> 31:08.198
His sister.

31:08.350 --> 31:10.108
Well, I shouldn't say
my sister,

31:10.202 --> 31:12.536
but I'm gonna say
my sister Brittney.

31:12.763 --> 31:16.290
-BRITTNEY: Oh!
-She surprises me every day.

31:17.267 --> 31:21.211
But...Justin surprises me more,

31:21.363 --> 31:25.607
his talent,
his body awareness,

31:25.700 --> 31:28.960
annoying how fast
he picks up choreography.

31:29.054 --> 31:30.721
Justin's undeniable.

31:30.872 --> 31:32.114
(applause)

31:32.132 --> 31:33.390
I might have looked
a little tough

31:33.617 --> 31:34.540
in the premiere,

31:34.801 --> 31:37.728
but the truth is,
I'm a sucker for romance.

31:37.955 --> 31:40.805
<i> Reggie, got any hot goss?</i>
<i> Dish.</i>

31:40.958 --> 31:42.382
Who are you right now?

31:42.401 --> 31:43.934
REGGIE:
Oh, no, my lips are sealed.

31:44.086 --> 31:46.311
Oh, come on, man.
Spill the tea.

31:46.463 --> 31:48.630
-You really wanna know?
-WAYNE: Mm.

31:48.649 --> 31:50.556
-REGGIE: America?
-AUDIENCE: Yes!

31:50.651 --> 31:52.651
BOTH: Yes!

31:53.561 --> 31:56.488
All right, all right,
all right, maybe just a little.

31:56.582 --> 31:57.822
Roll it.

31:57.917 --> 32:01.401
<i> (soft piano music playing)</i>

32:01.420 --> 32:03.903
See my girls
in the second row right there?

32:03.997 --> 32:05.088
PAULA: Yeah.

32:05.257 --> 32:06.481
They look like
they're having fun.

32:06.500 --> 32:10.076
They better.
Thank you, by the way.

32:10.095 --> 32:11.503
Hey, are you okay?

32:11.655 --> 32:13.096
The other night when you were
talking on the phone

32:13.323 --> 32:14.489
with your doctor,
you seemed like--

32:14.582 --> 32:16.007
Yeah, yeah, it's okay.
That's just test stuff.

32:16.160 --> 32:17.159
It's okay.
I'm fine.

32:17.177 --> 32:19.585
-You sure?
-Yeah.

32:19.605 --> 32:22.013
<i> ♪ </i>

32:22.166 --> 32:25.776
(cheers and applause)

32:25.927 --> 32:29.688
Mike and Paula, I don't want
to read too much

32:29.782 --> 32:34.176
into that fire escape dancing,
but is there something there?

32:34.269 --> 32:35.677
Anything's possible.

32:35.770 --> 32:38.604
We're just friends.
That's it.

32:38.624 --> 32:40.106
Huh.

32:40.125 --> 32:42.275
-Well, there you have it.
-All right.

32:42.369 --> 32:44.519
There is dancing.
There's romance.

32:44.538 --> 32:45.462
There's an NFL player.

32:45.613 --> 32:47.706
-REGGIE: Yes, there is.
-(laughter)

32:47.800 --> 32:49.357
But at its core,

32:49.451 --> 32:52.970
<i> The Big Leap</i>
is about second chances.

32:53.121 --> 32:54.879
<i> (light music playing)</i>

32:54.974 --> 32:55.973
<i> Gabby, I'm sorry,</i>
<i> but this</i>

32:56.124 --> 32:57.307
<i> is the end of the road</i>
<i> for you.</i>

32:57.459 --> 33:00.644
<i> ♪ </i>

33:00.795 --> 33:03.221
Please fasten your seat belts
and return your tray tables

33:03.373 --> 33:04.982
to their upright position.

33:05.133 --> 33:06.799
Almost home, everybody.

33:06.893 --> 33:10.136
(cheers and applause)

33:10.155 --> 33:14.065
Now, Gabby and Reggie,
can you talk about

33:14.218 --> 33:17.068
how you've helped
each other reach new heights?

33:17.221 --> 33:20.146
Yeah, I needed her.

33:20.315 --> 33:21.999
Gabby's been
really patient with me,

33:22.226 --> 33:24.242
and I couldn't have asked
for a better partner.

33:24.394 --> 33:28.913
Yeah, I felt 100%
supported by Reggie,

33:29.066 --> 33:31.324
literally and figuratively.

33:31.343 --> 33:33.159
(laughter)

33:33.253 --> 33:35.570
Now, the last question
is for Brittney.

33:35.663 --> 33:37.163
I never approved
a question for Brittney.

33:37.182 --> 33:38.682
Who changed my script?

33:38.909 --> 33:40.909
Hey, Wayne, let's get out
of this question and throw

33:40.927 --> 33:42.410
to the Motown package--
copy that, please.

33:42.429 --> 33:45.171
And being so accomplished
and blessed

33:45.265 --> 33:49.008
with such incredible genes
from your mother's side,

33:49.102 --> 33:51.844
how and where do you find
your inspiration?

33:51.864 --> 33:54.698
<i> (soft music)</i>

33:54.849 --> 34:01.204
Well, I'm inspired by my mother
and by Simon, of course.

34:01.356 --> 34:06.359
But I've been really impressed
with my new friend Gabby.

34:06.378 --> 34:07.435
AUDIENCE: Aw.

34:07.454 --> 34:10.789
BRITTNEY:
Yeah, she's a young woman.

34:10.941 --> 34:12.549
She had to give up on her dream

34:12.700 --> 34:14.609
because she had a baby
with her high school teacher,

34:14.628 --> 34:18.947
and her resilience
is really inspiring to me.

34:18.965 --> 34:20.131
Love you, Gabs.

34:20.225 --> 34:21.466
The hell is wrong
with you, girl?

34:21.560 --> 34:23.209
-How could you say that?
-Did you know about this?

34:23.228 --> 34:24.286
No, no, I swear.
I didn't know about this.

34:24.304 --> 34:25.395
Why would you say that?

34:25.622 --> 34:27.639
-Girl, what is your issue?
-That's messed up.

34:27.791 --> 34:30.883
Okay, I really don't like
calling other women a bitch,

34:30.903 --> 34:33.070
but what a bitch!

34:33.221 --> 34:35.130
Student-teacher relationship?

34:35.148 --> 34:36.222
We had a whole meeting
about this.

34:36.316 --> 34:37.465
I know.

34:37.559 --> 34:39.317
We were not going to talk
about this.

34:39.486 --> 34:40.911
What do we do?

34:41.062 --> 34:42.245
-MAN: Wow, not cool.
-Hey, guys.

34:42.472 --> 34:44.122
<i> Let's if Gabby</i>
<i> wants to respond.</i>

34:44.232 --> 34:47.459
Gabby, would you like
to respond?

34:48.754 --> 34:52.339
Yeah, I would.
Thank you.

34:53.500 --> 34:56.593
Brittney, that was not
your secret to tell.

34:56.820 --> 34:59.078
You know, there is a reason
you don't have any friends.

34:59.098 --> 35:04.417
You are a vain,
scared, lonely person

35:04.586 --> 35:08.163
who needs to tear others down
to seem interesting.

35:08.181 --> 35:09.940
All I did
was answer the question.

35:10.016 --> 35:11.683
(audience booing)

35:11.835 --> 35:13.944
Oh, I didn't know I wasn't
allowed to speak Gabby's truth.

35:14.095 --> 35:15.403
I'm sorry.

35:16.431 --> 35:19.116
Who threw that?
That was assault.

35:19.267 --> 35:20.358
Oh!

35:20.510 --> 35:23.678
-Oh, hell no!
-What are you guys doing?

35:23.697 --> 35:25.847
-Brittney, you don't do that!
-Ladies, break it up.

35:25.940 --> 35:28.458
No, I just wanna talk to her.
Do you understand me?

35:28.685 --> 35:30.776
-Should we go to Motown?
-No, not yet.

35:30.796 --> 35:32.111
Stay on Brittney.

35:32.131 --> 35:33.547
<i> Now give me Gabby.</i>

35:34.616 --> 35:35.799
You're making it worse!

35:35.968 --> 35:37.417
<i> NICK: Find Justin for me.</i>

35:37.527 --> 35:39.302
I need a reaction shot
of Reggie.

35:39.972 --> 35:41.212
<i> Guys, Miriam's down.</i>

35:41.306 --> 35:42.455
Now I need a wide
of the cast, guys.

35:42.474 --> 35:44.123
I need a wide of the cast.
There you go.

35:44.201 --> 35:45.216
Hey, hey, cue up
the Motown package.

35:45.369 --> 35:46.726
But you wait for my word.
Hear me?

35:47.962 --> 35:50.054
Really feels like it's time
to go to Motown.

35:50.131 --> 35:51.481
-You good?
-I'm fine, I'm fine.

35:51.633 --> 35:53.541
Okay, everybody.
She's good, she's good.

35:53.560 --> 35:55.134
RAVEN: Oh, yeah.
She's good, everybody.

35:55.154 --> 35:59.656
-She's fine.
-Ahh!

35:59.807 --> 36:01.307
Okay, let's to Motown.

36:01.326 --> 36:04.578
<i> SINGER: ♪ Ain't no mountain</i>
<i> high, ain't no valley low ♪</i>

36:08.333 --> 36:10.241
You should have
gone to Motown.

36:10.335 --> 36:12.243
You should have gone
to the hospital.

36:12.396 --> 36:13.578
I knew what I was doing.

36:13.730 --> 36:15.338
I mean, as soon
as the twins' crazy mom

36:15.490 --> 36:17.007
hijacked the teleprompter,
I followed the story.

36:17.234 --> 36:18.824
I couldn't help myself.

36:18.919 --> 36:20.402
You followed it
straight off a cliff!

36:20.570 --> 36:23.071
Months of work, and this is all
anyone's going to remember.

36:23.089 --> 36:25.423
(laughs)

36:25.517 --> 36:28.426
That was great.
Can you believe it?

36:28.578 --> 36:31.262
A reality show
about ballet is trending.

36:31.431 --> 36:33.690
Brittney is already a meme.

36:33.841 --> 36:37.343
That girl's got star power.
Why the poopy faces?

36:37.362 --> 36:38.678
We're having a funeral
for dignity.

36:38.697 --> 36:42.273
-I feel bad about Gabby.
-A shred of humanity.

36:42.426 --> 36:44.016
Well, better late than never,
I guess.

36:44.110 --> 36:46.110
Guys, that was a success.

36:46.205 --> 36:49.188
It was juicy
and sticky and noisy.

36:49.282 --> 36:51.357
Yesterday nobody even knew
what<i> The Big Leap</i> was,

36:51.376 --> 36:52.434
and today they do.

36:52.436 --> 36:56.862
And Nick is being
received...warmly.

36:56.882 --> 36:59.274
Like...(clears throat)
"Forget about<i> Atlantis"</i> warmly?

36:59.276 --> 37:01.367
Nobody's ever gonna forget
about that, ever.

37:01.386 --> 37:03.553
But add this to the stack
of greatest hits.

37:03.705 --> 37:09.117
Nobody serves up
a hot-ass mess like you, Nick.

37:09.135 --> 37:10.452
Great.
Put that on my tombstone.

37:10.470 --> 37:12.044
We couldn't even
get through a Q&A.

37:12.064 --> 37:13.621
How are we gonna
get through<i> Swan Lake?</i>

37:13.640 --> 37:17.141
Not to be prescriptive,
but if<i> Swan Lake</i>

37:17.294 --> 37:20.553
turned into just a giant brawl

37:20.572 --> 37:23.648
and people are just grabbing
at tutus and biting faces,

37:23.800 --> 37:27.077
I'm gonna watch that,
and so is my daughter.

37:27.228 --> 37:30.321
That's good TV.
Nick, top-notch.

37:30.398 --> 37:32.307
I should have gone to Motown.

37:32.325 --> 37:34.251
You should probably go
to the hospital, yeah?

37:34.402 --> 37:36.494
This could not have worked out
better for us, baby.

37:36.646 --> 37:40.632
This is from Gabby,
before you blew up her life.

37:42.076 --> 37:44.910
Simon, can you please
celebrate your sister?

37:44.930 --> 37:47.514
She's trending.

37:49.417 --> 37:52.844
-(phone chimes)
-Ah! (laughs)

37:52.996 --> 37:55.921
<i> (dramatic music)</i>

37:55.999 --> 38:00.926
<i> ♪ </i>

38:00.946 --> 38:02.946
Is this why you did that?

38:03.097 --> 38:05.824
Mom told me to, why?

38:05.933 --> 38:09.177
<i> ♪ </i>

38:09.195 --> 38:12.497
Lovewells against the world,
right?

38:13.775 --> 38:15.458
I don't--

38:17.445 --> 38:18.870
No, Brittney.

38:19.022 --> 38:23.207
<i> ♪ </i>

38:23.360 --> 38:26.011
What's the matter with him?

38:27.455 --> 38:30.031
Mom, I did not know
you could move like that.

38:30.050 --> 38:31.533
Yeah, you were
so light on your feet.

38:31.551 --> 38:32.642
I keep telling you guys,

38:32.794 --> 38:34.293
your mom used to be
a pretty good dancer.

38:34.462 --> 38:37.129
No, no, I mean when you dodged
that water bottle,

38:37.149 --> 38:38.672
I mean, you were like a cat.

38:38.708 --> 38:40.466
Yeah, that was a close one,
wasn't it?

38:40.560 --> 38:42.485
All of my friends
are texting me.

38:42.562 --> 38:44.395
I mean, they're all
gonna watch the show.

38:44.489 --> 38:47.048
And your dancing
was pretty cool too.

38:47.067 --> 38:50.643
<i> ♪ </i>

38:50.662 --> 38:54.331
GINA: Boy, that Brittney turned
out to be a real piece of work.

38:56.076 --> 38:58.059
Are you okay?

38:58.152 --> 39:00.003
Not really.

39:00.230 --> 39:02.154
Poor Sammy.

39:02.174 --> 39:03.898
This is gonna
follow me everywhere

39:03.917 --> 39:05.425
for the rest of my life.

39:06.845 --> 39:08.736
(sighs)

39:08.755 --> 39:11.723
Hey, look at me.

39:16.021 --> 39:19.414
This is one thing
that happened in your life,

39:19.432 --> 39:24.752
and it gave us Sammy,
but it does not define you.

39:24.771 --> 39:27.346
That teacher is a creep
and a predator.

39:27.366 --> 39:34.278
You are a talented,
beautiful, fantastic woman.

39:34.355 --> 39:37.207
And I am so proud
to be your mother.

39:37.358 --> 39:39.784
I only wish you would've
told me when it was happening,

39:39.936 --> 39:44.029
and I would've spent the last
seven years telling you that.

39:44.049 --> 39:48.259
And I'm so sorry
that you were so alone.

39:49.537 --> 39:50.970
Oh, Mom.

39:53.283 --> 39:57.227
Gabby!
Gabby, I am so sorry.

39:57.454 --> 40:00.638
Brittney's a mess.
My mom's a monster.

40:00.790 --> 40:02.023
This is for you.

40:05.795 --> 40:07.812
What is that?

40:07.906 --> 40:11.449
It's a note from Reggie.

40:12.861 --> 40:14.819
(knock at door)

40:14.988 --> 40:18.139
<i> ("Ain't No Mountain</i>
<i> High Enough")</i>

40:18.158 --> 40:20.232
Justin, I swear.
I didn't know.

40:20.326 --> 40:21.809
No?

40:21.828 --> 40:24.069
'Cause your family
seems super tight-knit.

40:24.089 --> 40:25.663
Look, it's hard
to explain, okay?

40:25.815 --> 40:28.091
But it was just
the three of us growing up,

40:28.318 --> 40:30.242
and we moved around a lot,

40:30.262 --> 40:34.914
and my mom has got
this power over us.

40:34.933 --> 40:36.674
So she told me
to push you away.

40:36.826 --> 40:41.938
And I did because
I'm a mama's boy,

40:42.165 --> 40:43.940
and my mom is a cult leader.

40:44.109 --> 40:48.319
So that's me.

40:49.114 --> 40:50.655
I have some stuff too.

40:53.100 --> 40:55.452
You saw my dad.

40:55.603 --> 40:58.288
You read me right
from the beginning.

40:58.439 --> 40:59.681
<i> SINGERS: ♪ If you're my goal </i>

40:59.774 --> 41:00.940
(exhales heavily)

41:00.959 --> 41:03.184
I've never hooked up
with another man sober.

41:03.277 --> 41:05.110
<i> SINGERS: ♪ No wind, no rain </i>

41:05.130 --> 41:09.373
So...that's me.

41:09.468 --> 41:12.193
<i> SINGERS: ♪ If you want to go </i>

41:12.286 --> 41:16.306
Well, have you had anything
to drink tonight?

41:16.533 --> 41:17.957
<i> ♪ </i>

41:17.976 --> 41:22.127
<i> SINGERS: ♪ Oh-oh-oh-oh </i>

41:22.296 --> 41:27.967
<i> ♪ Oh-oh-oh-oh-oh </i>

41:28.135 --> 41:31.321
<i> ♪ Ooh </i>

41:31.548 --> 41:34.565
<i> ♪ Ooh-ooh-ooh </i>

41:34.718 --> 41:38.143
<i> ♪ </i>

41:38.163 --> 41:41.889
<i> ♪ I know, but remember </i>

41:41.908 --> 41:43.482
(knocking)

41:43.502 --> 41:45.409
<i> SINGER: ♪ If you should</i>
<i> fall short of your desires ♪</i>

41:45.504 --> 41:47.987
-Hi.
-Mike, now's not a good time.

41:48.006 --> 41:52.083
I need to tell you without
the cameras and the craziness

41:52.235 --> 41:54.569
that I am sorry
for how I acted.

41:54.620 --> 41:55.753
I'm an idiot.

41:55.997 --> 41:58.348
I'm sick of being angry
and getting in my own way.

41:58.499 --> 42:00.575
And I just wanna move forward
with my life.

42:00.593 --> 42:04.979
And I think that maybe
that life includes you.

42:06.007 --> 42:09.767
So...can we give it a shot?

42:09.919 --> 42:11.844
<i> ♪ </i>

42:12.013 --> 42:13.846
I'm sorry.

42:13.940 --> 42:16.199
What I said
on the show was real.

42:17.536 --> 42:22.038
We're just friends,
and that's all we're gonna be.

42:23.024 --> 42:24.782
I gotta go.

42:24.876 --> 42:28.044
<i> SINGERS:</i>
<i> ♪ No river wide enough </i>

42:28.195 --> 42:30.121
<i> ♪ To keep me from you </i>

42:30.215 --> 42:33.441
<i> ♪ Ain't no mountain</i>
<i> high enough ♪</i>

42:33.459 --> 42:34.700
(knocking)

42:34.719 --> 42:38.112
<i> ♪ Nothing can keep me,</i>
<i> keep me from you ♪</i>

42:38.131 --> 42:40.965
Hey, you okay?

42:41.117 --> 42:42.392
(sighs)

42:42.543 --> 42:43.968
You wanna come inside?

42:44.137 --> 42:45.453
Yeah, yeah, I'm good.
I'm good.

42:45.471 --> 42:46.470
I don't wanna talk
about that right now.

42:46.565 --> 42:48.881
Did you write this?

42:48.975 --> 42:52.068
Yeah, yeah, I did.

42:52.219 --> 42:53.719
Do you mean it?

42:53.813 --> 42:56.322
Oh, yeah.

42:57.558 --> 43:00.318
Little dinosaur is not me,
though.

43:00.470 --> 43:03.304
<i> SINGERS: ♪ Ain't no valley</i>
<i> low enough ♪</i>

43:03.397 --> 43:05.323
<i> ♪ Ain't no river wide enough </i>

43:05.475 --> 43:09.102
<i> ♪ Nothing can keep me,</i>
<i> keep me from you ♪</i>

43:09.104 --> 43:11.662
<i> ♪ Nothing in this world </i>

43:11.815 --> 43:15.675
<i> ♪ Nothing in this world</i>
<i> can keep me from you ♪</i>
